HEADWORD: Pyrope
<hw>Pyr"ope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pyropus</ets>
a kind of red bronze, fr. Gr. <?/; <?/ fire + <?/ the eye, face: cf. F.
<ets>pyrope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A variety of garnet, of
a poppy or blood-red color, frequently with a tinge of orange. It is
used as a gem. See the Note under <er>Garnet</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

